cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.IR 

This paper is about improving the consistency of translations in the context of a document, which is a common problem in natural language processing. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with natural language processing. The paper also proposes a monolingual sequence-to-sequence model, which falls under the categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the model uses neural networks, which is a common technique in cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper deals with improving the accuracy of machine translation, which is a subfield of cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
